description.narrative: UNICEFInnocenti’s Research on Education and Development (READ) unitgenerated and supported the use of quality research to address the global learning crisis and ensure every child learns. In 2021, READ conducted demand-driven, country-level research spanning foundational learning, digital learning and innovation, teachers, early childhood education, inclusive education for children with disabilities, sport for development, and gender. Across these thematic areas, READ maintains an equity focus, generating evidence on what works for the most vulnerable children.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:24/03/2022
